comment.body:
@nandan2003 thanks for the PR, I did not have time to look at it but set the label "Waiting for reviewer" hoping another maintainer will have a closer look.

In the mean time, please:
- add a changelog entry to explain what the fix is doing see https://github.com/scikit-learn/scikit-learn/blob/main/doc/whats_new/upcoming_changes/README.md for how to do it
- keep the changes minimal, in particular revert unrelated changes like adding `r` in front of strings or renaming variables with leading underscore. This feels very much like an LLM did that for you and you did not take the time to clean-up. As a maintainer in this age where we get plenty of seemingly low-effort LLM-driven contributions, this makes me grumpy and less likely to look at your PR.

@dkobak thanks a lot for the first review, this is very useful!

